FBIS3-53557 "drnes011_j_94024" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen President Salih, Iraqi Envoy Discuss Arab Issues JN1801091294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 2000 GMT 17 Jan 94 JN1801091294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council chairman, today received brother Muhsin Khalil, the Iraqi ambassador to our country. During the meeting, discussions dealt with relations between the two fraternal countries and issues and developments of interest to the Arab nation. During the meeting, the Iraqi ambassador stated that fraternal Iraq is eager to see our country overcome the current situation and challenges. He indicated that Yemeni unity is a source of pride and hope for all Arabs. He said that it is the responsibility of the entire Arab nation to maintain this unity. The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned that the brother Presidential Council chairman has asked the brother ambassador to convey a message to his brother Iraqi President Saddam Husayn on the fraternal relations and issues and developments of interest to the Arab nation.
